1. Edit /etc/apt/sources.list
	- comment out "deb cdrom:[Debian GNU/Linux...." with a #	
	- add " contrib non-free" after main
2.This step is just good pratice	
	sudo update
	sudo upgrade
	sudo dist-upgrade
3. For Network Manager		

Edit file
/etc/network/interfaces

Wired Network nic interface
For correct behaviour on NetworkManager comment out the whole file. Each line with '#'

4. Build the wifimodule (before done in a script, but gives error)
Open a shell and do
	a. apt -y install linux-image-$(uname -r|sed 's,[^-]*-[^-]*-,,') linux-headers-$(uname -r|sed 's,[^-]*-[^-]*-,,') broadcom-sta-dkms
	b. modprobe -r b44 b43 b43legacy ssb brcmsmac bcma
	c. modprobe wl
